s.
    Then, since (20) holds, whichever way the if-clause on lines 8, 9 of Find-MDL evaluates to, what is returned on line 11 or line 13 will still be a (sub)model with the minimum description length, completing the inductive step.
    It is easy to see that the running time of the algorithm is linear in both the number of leaf nodes of the input thesaurus tree and the input sample size.
